main event: A civilian reported a UFO sighting in Dayton, Ohio on November 5, 1966, observing one object for 50 minutes that moved in a ground visual manner.
interesting points: The object was observed moving toward the northeast while blinking on and off at high speed, similar to characteristics of a meteor., The sighting duration was noted as unusually long at 50 minutes for such an object., Multiple reports from civilians existed for the same time period and location., The sighting was dismissed as insufficient data for evaluation by the United States Air Force., The object showed characteristics inconsistent with typical aircraft behavior.
